-- Toyota dealer in Japan: carmaker plans Prius recall
-- 
-- Sat Feb 6, 2010 11:05pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/02/07/us-toyota-recall-prius-idUSTRE61606I20100207

 

 TOYOTA CITY, Japan  (Reuters) - A Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) dealer said on Sunday the automaker had informed him of its plans to recall the third-generation Prius cars in Japan as early as the next few days because of a braking glitch. 

 The dealer, on the outskirts of Toyota City in central Japan, declined to be identified. Toyota was not immediately available to comment. (Reporting by  Taiga Uranaka  and  Nathan Layne ; Editing by  Nick Macfie )